Moldavian Subcarpathians

Moldavian Subcarpatians () is a geographic area spanning in the NE of Romania, situated to the east of the Eastern Carpathian Mountains. The subcarpathians are considered to be part of the Moldavian Plateau. They are composed of:
Moldavian Subcarpathians are separated from the rest of the Moldavian Plateau by the Siret and Moldova River Valleys (north and east), and are bounded by the Curvature Subcarpathians () to the south.

