Eric Moyo

Eric Moyo (born 1982, Zimbabwe) is a Zimbabwaen singer and the first ever winner of "Idols East Africa" a version of the Idol series. As part of the recording contract, Moyo is also assured of US$25,000 in guaranteed album sales from the telecompany Celtel. He also won a 42-inch LG plasma television set.

